### Rendering a React component into an existing HTML element

Source: https://github.com/reactjs/react.dev/blob/main/src/content/learn/add-react-to-an-existing-project.md

Demonstrates how to integrate a React component into a specific HTML element on a page, preserving existing HTML content.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head><title>My app</title></head>
  <body>
    <p>This paragraph is a part of HTML.</p>
    <nav id="navigation"></nav>
    <p>This paragraph is also a part of HTML.</p>
  </body>
</html>
```

```js
import { createRoot } from 'react-dom/client';

function NavigationBar() {
  // TODO: Actually implement a navigation bar
  return <h1>Hello from React!</h1>;
}

const domNode = document.getElementById('navigation');
const root = createRoot(domNode);
root.render(<NavigationBar />);
```

